          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sample consisted of a carbon substrate made of",
                "pyrolytic graphite, and was covered with layers of",
                "Al/2-O/3 (174.6 nanometers) and Au (10.0 nanometers) on",
                "top.  The Al/2-O/3 layer was deposited by filtered",
                "vacuum arc from a pure aluminium cathode in oxygen",
                "atmosphere.  The gold film was deposited by electron",
                "beam evaporation and was used as an internal dose",
                "reference.  The thicknesses of the layers were",
                "determined by 4He ion backscattering at 2023 KeV",
                "incident energy.  The atomic ratio of oxygen to",
                "aluminium was determined to be 3:2 with an accuracy  of",
                "2%.  A pure carbon sample was used to examine the",
                "background due to nuclear reactions of incident Li ions",
                "with the carbon substrate."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " PIPS Detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERGAR"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "  The terminal voltage of the accelerator",
                "was calibrated with the well-known resonances of",
                "the 27Al(p,g)28Si reaction at 992 and 1380 KeV.  The",
                "energy spread of the beam is below 1 KeV for protons at",
                "1000 KeV and is assumed to be of the same order for Li",
                "ions, which are produced with the same source."
              ]
            }
          ],
